args:
The prince and his friends save a woman
named Felicia from a fiend attack. She then
convinces the group to help her rescue a
dragon who used himself as bait while she
made good her escape.
In the skies above a forest...
The veil of darkness is torn asunder by a roar\nas a fearsome black dragon emerges with a\nlovely woman on his back.
They gently glide toward the ground,\nseemingly without a care in the world.
Do not concern yourself with what\nlies behind us, Felicia.
With that grievous wound, he will be\nunable to give chase.
But Phantom, I still hear his voice.\nThose...horrible, teasing whispers.
'Tis nothing more than the sound of\nthe wind—and there is no need to\nfear such invisible terrors.
But regardless of what may come,\nI swear you shall remain free.
Thank you, Phantom. I'm certain it\nwill all be okay...
Fly, my sweet! Fly as fast and far as\nyou will! It matters not, for you have\nno home to return to!
You shall never escape me,\nmy beloved dancer...
Blue skies! Warm sun! Chirping birds!\nThis is perfect date weather, my darling!
That IS what we're doing here, yes?
Seeing as how it's just the two of us\nhere in this open field...
Hey, what're we? Chopped lizard gizzard?\n...Yeah, she ain't payin' attention.
I'm actually impressed she's somehow\nable to turn the end of a fiend-slaying\nexpedition into a date.

Truly, Mym, what happened to the dignity
you possessed at the volcano? You're no
better than a daffy maiden experiencing
the throes of first love.
Er, perhaps we should all remain more\nfocused on the issues at hand?
A-after all, there may not be fiends about\nNOW, but that does not mean we should\ndrop our guards with...dates and so forth.
My my, Elisanne! What's all this?\nMight you be...JEALOUS?
Easy, everyone. Look, I get what Elly is\nsaying—we always need to keep our\neyes peeled for danger.
But if we stay in a state of constant\nemergency, we'll wear ourselves out.\nThe secret is to find a happy medium.
I'm not sure if you're missing the point\non purpose, but I suppose I can go\nalong with this for now.
Th-that's right! Moderation in all things\nis key! Sweet, sweet moderation...
Are we SURE the prince is as smart\nas we all give him credit for?
If he understood women, this argument\nwould have been resolved long ago.
Just relax, darling. I adore that naive part\nof you as much as every other—
N-no! Don't come any closer!\nI don't want to go back!
And we're gonna save her! Haaah!
I know you just risked everything to save\nme, but may I ask your help to rescue\nsomeone else?
He's a dragon, and he's being attacked\nby a fiend right as we speak!
He used himself as bait to allow me\ntime to escape.
And if I don't find some way to help him,\nPhantom is going to...
I know how presumptuous this sounds\nafter you just saved me, but I don't know\nwhat else to do!
So I beg of you, help me save Phantom!
There's no need to beg. We'll help.
Of course! We would never leave a\ndragon in their hour of need.
Oh, this is such a relief...
In that case, please follow me. This way!
(She definitely said Phantom,\nbut it can't be... Right?)
You shall never escape me,\nmy beloved dancer...
